body: I feel 100% different but still feeling weak. I finished working outside around 430iah abd by 530 i was fubar. author: HM3-LPO
body: I knew you were a young man with a young family but heatstroke/sickness is serious at any age. I was a Hospital Corpsman in the Navy for eight years and saw plenty of it. When I was young I hung drywall for a contractor and that is some very labor intensive work (especially in a hot environment). Take it easy today boss. I don't need to tell you to get rest and plenty of liquids. Happy Labor Day to you!

author: NihilistHUGZ
body: Yeah I'm only 34 and it tears me up quick. I couldn't believe my basic yardwork, weedeat and mow, got me so good. I was laid in the bottom of my shower just sick as a dog when it hit me. I guess I had stayed hydrated, but had so much on my mind from my granny passing that I forgot to eat. Thank you for the kind words and my wife is home with me and she is mum'ing me good. Happy Labor Day!
